13 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the stricken title, enacting clause, and
entire bill and insert:
14
15
16 "An Act relating to tourism; amending 74 O.S. 2021,
Section 2251, which relates to the Oklahoma Tourism
17 and Recreation Department Revolving Fund; amending
properties of the fund; declaring funds appropriated;
18 determining interest stays within the fund; creating
the Real Property Proceeds Revolving Fund;
19 establishing revolving fund characteristics;
declaring funds appropriated; determining interest
20 stays within the fund; providing for codification;
and providing an effective date.
21
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 248 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 2251, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 2251. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
4 a revolving fund for the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department
5 to be designated the “Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department
6 Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
7 to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received
8 by the Department pursuant to the provisions of this act, monies
9 derived from the sale or conveyance of real property under the
10 jurisdiction of the Commission, and interest attributable to
11 investment of money in the fund. The revolving fund shall be a
12 continuing fund not subject to fiscal year limitations and shall be
13 under the administrative direction of the Department. Expenditures
14 from the fund created by this section shall be for the
15 administration, operation, and maintenance expenses of the
16 Department, for purchase of real property, and shall be made
17 pursuant to the laws of this state and the statutes relating to the
18 Department. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
19 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
20 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
21 Services for approval and payment the Oklahoma Tourism, Parks and
22 Recreation Enhancement Act. All monies accruing to the credit of
23 the fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by
24 the Department for the administration, operation, and maintenance
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 248 Page 2

1 expe nses of the Department, for purchase of real property, and shall
2 be made pursuant to the laws of this state. Expenditures from the
3 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
4 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
5 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
6 payment.
7 B. Notwithstanding any provision of law, all interest and
8 income derived from deposits to the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation
9 Department Revolving Fund shall be credited to the Oklahoma Tourism
10 and Recreation Department Revolving Fund.
11 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2251.1 of Title 74, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
15 fund for the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department to be
16 designated the “Real Property Proceeds Revolving Fund”. The fund
17 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
18 and shall consist of all monies derived from the sale, transfer,
19 lease, or other conveyance of real property under the jurisdiction
20 of the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Commission, except those
21 leases entered into pursuant to a concessionaire agreement. All
22 monies accruing to the fund are hereby appropriated and may be
23 expended by the Department for maintenance and capital projects
24 included on the annually updated five-year plan approved by the
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 248 Page 3

1 Long -Range Capital Planning Commission pursuant to Section 188A of
2 Title 73 of the Oklahoma Statutes; provided, such monies shall not
3 be expended for compensation of any employee of a state agency. No
4 monies from the fund shall be transferred for any purpose to any
5 other state agency. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon
6 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
7 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
8 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
9 B. Notwithstanding any provision of law, all interest and
10 income derived from deposits to the Real Property Proceeds Revolving
11 Fund shall be credited to the Real Property Proceeds Revolving Fund.
12 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026."
13 Passed the House of Representatives the 6th day of May, 2026.
